Nginx is **extremely lightweight** compared to most web servers, but the *minimum system requirements* depend on **how you plan to use it** (static files, proxy, or high-load API gateway).

Letâ€™s break it down clearly ðŸ‘‡

---

## ðŸ§© 1. **Absolute Minimum (for learning or small local use)**

You can run Nginx even on **tiny systems**.

| Resource       | Minimum                                                            |
| -------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **CPU**        | 1 core (x86, ARM, etc.)                                            |
| **RAM**        | 64 MB (bare minimum)                                               |
| **Disk space** | ~5 MB for binary + 10â€“20 MB for logs/config                        |
| **OS**         | Any Linux (Ubuntu, Debian, Alpine, CentOS), BSD, macOS, or Windows |

ðŸ’¡ Even **OpenWRT routers** and **Raspberry Pi Zero** can run Nginx.

Example (Alpine Linux + Nginx):

```bash
apk add nginx
```

This installs it in < 3 MB.

